vectorData.altText: 3. Which cell is derived from blood monocytes?
That's right!  Microglia are phagocytic cells of the macrophage / monocyte cell lineage.
That is incorrect. Click here      to learn the answer, then come back to try again.

Microglia are phagocytic cells of the macrophage / monocyte cell lineage. 
Normally they are few in number (~5^%^ of glia) but when activated by damage, or infection they proliferate and become phagocytic.
Diffuse microgliosis results in the large number of microglial cells seen here with H&E. Notice the elongated nuclei of the microglia.
